<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8281731>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Lissodendoryx (Waldoschmittia) almeidai sp. nov., holotype. A, preserved specimen (UFPEPOR 2724); B, detail of small fistule; C, internal part of sponge filled with debris; D, cross section showing choanosome and ectosome; E, ectosomal brushes of tylotes; F, oxeas in choanosome; G, oxea; H, tylote; I, detail of the extremity of the oxea; J, detail of the end of the tylote; K, arcuate isochelae. Scales: A = 1.5 cm; D = 300 µm; E–F = 40 µm G = 20 µm; H = 10 µm; I = 50 µm; J–K = 5 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8281731/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

